          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1581614375610-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables are tender, drain your<strong> king prawns</strong>, then add them<strong> </strong>to the pan with 2/3 of the<strong> speedy sambal</strong> (save the rest for later!)</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and<strong> toasted sesame oil</strong> and cook for 4-5 min further or until the prawns are cooked through</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1581614380022-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1581614380022-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1581614380022-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1581614380022-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1581614380022-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain the<strong> cooked noodles</strong> and add them to the pan with the prawns and vegetables</p><p>Gently stir everything together for 1-2 min or until the noodles are fully coated in the sauce – this is your <strong>king prawn mie goreng</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1581614384328-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
